<TITLE> 51 testify in Aug 21 grenade attack twin cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka May 11 (bdnews24.com)Fifty-one witnesses have testified in the Aug 21, 2004 grenade attack twin cases. Five witnesses who testified on behalf of the state on Monday were Sumon Bhowmik, Faruq Ahmed, Dilip Ghose , Apurba Chandra Das and Mohiuddin Babul Special tribunal judge Md Mazdar Hossain fixed the next date for hearing on Wednesday. Special public prosecutor Syed Rezaur Rahman said they would try to conclude the two cases within the specified time. If the case could not tried under any circumstances, they would go back to the previous court. In that case the government would issue a gazette again to bring the case under the special tribunal. Fourteen accused including former state minister Abdus Salam Pinto and Harkatul Jihad al_islami Bangladesh leader Mufti Abdul Hannan were produced in the court. Eight are absconding
